{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb3f37c3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s392"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"392"},"text":"§ 392.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Depositaries of Government funds as confined to banks in Federal reserve system; member banks as depositaries","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No public funds of the postal savings, or any Government funds, shall be deposited in the continental United States in any bank not belonging to the system established by this chapter: ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided, however","children":[],"tail":", That nothing in this chapter shall be construed to deny the right of the Secretary of the Treasury to use member banks as depositaries."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb3f37c4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s15"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 15","children":[],"tail":" (par.), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/265"},"text":"38 Stat. 265","children":[],"tail":"; Proc. No. 2695, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-07-04"},"text":"July 4, 1946","children":[],"tail":", 11 F.R. 7517, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/1352"},"text":"60 Stat. 1352","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb3f37c5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb3f37c6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddb3f37c7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6"},"text":"act Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/251"},"text":"38 Stat. 251","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Reserve Act. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see References in Text note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s226"},"text":"section 226 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb3f37c8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “of the Philippine Islands, or” after “No public funds” were deleted on authority of 1946 Proc. No. 2695, which granted independence to the Philippine Islands pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1394"},"text":"section 1394 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":". Proc. No. 2695 is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1394"},"text":"section 1394 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of second par. of section 15 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913","children":[],"tail":". Par. 1 of section 15 and par. 3 of section 15, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1923-03-04/ch252"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923, ch. 252","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 406, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/1480"},"text":"42 Stat. 1480","children":[],"tail":", are classified to sections 391 and 393, respectively, of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
